description: Borrowed from Latin victōriōsus, from victōria (“victory”), from victor (“conqueror”). Displaced native Old English siġefæst.

adjectives.description: victorious (comparative more victorious, superlative most victorious)

entries.meaning: Being the winner in a contest, struggle, war, etc.
examples: They will not force us, / They will stop degrading us, / They will not control us, / We will be victorious!

entries.meaning: Of or expressing a sense of victory or triumph.
examples: The team were met with a victorious cheer.
